The paper discusses community detection in multiplex networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. Based on the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper mentions social media analytics as one of the domains where multiplex networks are applied. The second most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a new algorithm for community detection. The third most likely sub-category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), as the paper deals with social networks. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses a random walk-based algorithm for community detection. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a node dissimilarity measure and uses clustering based on this distance.
